The enhanced PL for C60 on Py during spin pumping can be understood as well in terms of local dielectric changes. For molecules on metallic substrates, the electronic state excited by a photon may decay through non-radiative processes via dipole transfer to the metal (generation of eddy currents in Py) that does not contribute to the PL. The decay rate τ-1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
